content.description: The left arete that makes up the Twin Lizards Aretes.  Follow blocky terrain to a roof of sorts.  One large block in the roof seems kind of loose so tread lightly!
content.protection: TR this after making it up Twin Lizards proper.  If you don't feel up for the lead, you can solo a 4th class gully way to its right or other 4th class terrain even further right to gain the anchor on top of the pinnacle.

content.description:
A direct and very difficult start to Twin Lizards Arete.  Steep with slopey hands.

There is about a foot of climbing I haven't been able to figure out.  Shorter people may need a cheat stone to reach the first hold.  If you can get it let me know and I will update the FA.

A sport bolted arete that leads to a wild roof.  Traverse in from the left, bypassing the first bolt (it's for the hard direct start).  Head up the rough rock of the arete.  When higher up, pull out right to a ledge where the last bolt is clipped.  Pull the roof on its left side.  Instant exposure on this move.  Finish up and right to the rap anchor.
content.protection: 3 bolts to a rap anchor.  A little reachy/run out for sport climb but the hardest climbing is well protected.
content.location: The right arete of the Twin Lizards Aretes.
